  "prompt": "I am having problems with my friend. She is awesome, but she recently got a boyfriend. I just miss the way we once were. She's all over him and her other best friend. What should I do?",
  "response": "It's understandable to feel a bit left out or nostalgic when a friend enters a new relationship. Here are some steps you can take to navigate this situation:\n\n1. **Communicate Your Feelings**: Consider talking to your friend about how you've been feeling. Use \"I\" statements to express your emotions without sounding accusatory. For example, \"I miss the time we used to spend together\" can help convey your feelings without making her defensive.\n\n2. **Be Supportive**: Remember that this is an exciting time for her. Show support for her relationship by being happy for her. This can help strengthen your friendship in the long run.\n\n3. **Find Balance**: Try to adjust to the changes by finding a balance between spending time with her and making new memories. You can invite her to do things that include her boyfriend, or suggest hanging out with all of you together.\n\n4. **Expand Your Social Circle**: Use this time to strengthen other friendships or build new ones. This can help alleviate some of the feelings of being left out and broaden your support system.\n\n5. **Stay Patient**: Relationships often shift dynamics, but they can also evolve over time. It\u2019s possible that your friend will remain a close part of your life, even if it looks different for a while.\n\n6. **Focus on Yourself**: Invest time in your own interests and hobbies. This can boost your mood and may help you feel less dependent on the friendship for your happiness.\n\nRemember, change is a natural part of relationships, and it sometimes takes time to find a new rhythm.",
